HEADWORD: down-bow
<hw>down-bow</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Music)</fld> <def>a downward
stroke from the heel to the tip of the bow, in bowing a stringed
instrument. Contrasted with <contr>up-bow</contr>, when the bow is moved
in the opposite direction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

